      <story-so-far>
        <reasoning>The passage describes the formal evening meeting about Florence’s deception and its immediate consequences. I need to record that the group held a trial-like discussion, Florence admitted fabricating most of Elder Twist’s utterances (and that the fabrications began before Kira’s arrival), specific examples of what she falsified (nutrition, boundary compromise, resource plan), her rationale (used Elder Twist’s authority so people would listen), the group’s reactions (felt manipulated, trust broken), Holloway’s decision to ask Florence to separate from the group (temporary exile to another chamber, not a ban), Florence’s continued claim that her advice (including de-escalation) was sound, and that no operational decision was reached about the hostile plants—group fractured and urgent threat unresolved. I consolidated earlier items about Florence’s counsel: instead of listing her counsel as a separate approved action, I updated that those recommendations were attributed to Elder Twist but later revealed to be Florence’s fabrications. I kept high-priority ongoing facts (crash, SAM offline, glowing Biological Samples, Kira’s care, hostile boundary markings, collective commitment to self-reliance) and removed or merged redundant emotional/atmospheric details.</reasoning>
        <summary>
          - Shuttle carrying mining/terraforming supplies and a container labeled 'Biological Samples' struck the hull during approach and crashed; Kira Voss survived while several crew died.
          - Shipboard AI SAM remains offline; Kira’s neural link was activated and an assistant AI, Buddy, was instantiated; external communications and the ship’s distress beacon remain broken.
          - Hull breach exposed breathable atmosphere and alien vegetation; a local plant collective found and sheltered Kira and used the crashed shuttle as temporary shelter.
          - The active Biological Samples container continues to glow, draw power, and cannot be shut down.
          - Remedy (a salvage-built humanoid doctor) treated Kira’s leg and has iterated medical treatments; daily cooperative caregiving improved Kira’s condition.
          - The collective committed to self-reliance after external authorities (HR manuals, Elder Heartwood) failed to provide timely, usable guidance.
          - Scouts discovered deliberate, recent hostile boundary markings on the eastern perimeter—organized opposition by other plants that could force relocation and jeopardize Kira’s care.
          - Florence had been attributing tactical counsel to Elder Twist (including de-escalation, dietary guidance, and a resource-allocation plan) and the group had acted on that advice.
          - Formal evening meeting held to investigate Florence’s use of Elder Twist’s authority; Florence admitted she fabricated most of the elder’s 'wisdom,' saying the fabrications began before Kira’s arrival and continued for weeks.
          - Florence confessed specific falsifications (advice on human nutrition, a boundary compromise, and a resource allocation plan) and defended her actions as necessary to be heard and to produce good outcomes.
          - The group judged the behavior a violation of trust and manipulation despite the advice often producing positive results; Remedy and others emphasized that attribution and honesty matter.
          - Holloway asked Florence to separate from the main group temporarily (use other chambers) to give space for processing; Florence left claiming her hostile-plant de-escalation advice was still sound.
          - No operational consensus reached on how to respond to the hostile plants; the collective is fractured and uncertain how to reconcile Florence’s effective but dishonestly attributed counsel with the need to rebuild trust while addressing the external threat.
        </summary>
